{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default OpenSwiftUI views push position and size changes down"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"through the view hierarchy, so that only views that draw"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"something (known as leaf views) apply the current animation to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their frame rectangle. However in some cases this coalescing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior can give undesirable results; inserting a geometry"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group can correct that. A group acts as a barrier between the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view and its subviews, forcing the position and size"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values to be resolved and animated by the parent, before being"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed down to each subview."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example below shows one use of this function: ensuring that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the member views of each row in the stack apply (and animate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as) a single geometric transform from their ancestor view,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"rather than letting the effects of the ancestor views be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applied separately to each leaf view. If the members of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"ItemView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" may be added and removed at different times the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group ensures that they stay locked together as animations are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["VStack {","    ForEach(items) { item in","        ItemView(item: item)","            .geometryGroup()","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Returns: a new view whose geometry is isolated from that of its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parent view.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from its parent view."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/toggle\/geometrygroup()"]}],"metadata":{"platforms":[{"introducedAt":"13.0","beta":false,"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"iOS"},{"introducedAt":"10.15","beta":false,"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"macOS"},{"introducedAt":"13.0","beta":false,"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"tvOS"},{"introducedAt":"1.0","beta":false,"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"visionOS"},{"introducedAt":"6.0","beta":false,"unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"watchOS"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"geometryGroup"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","tex